election_record.label: New Hampshire 1810 U.S. House of Representatives

overview.note: New Hampshire law required a majority to elect for the U.S. House of Representatives. A 2nd Trial would be held in 1811.

sub_unit.name: Cheshire
sub_unit.note: Thomas W. Thompson received 4 votes as T. W. Thompson.

sub_unit.name: Fitzwilliam
sub_unit.note: John A. Harper received 61 votes as John H. Harper.

sub_unit.name: Lempster
sub_unit.note: John A. Harper received 35 votes as John A. Havin.

sub_unit.name: Marlborough
sub_unit.note: John A. Harper received 1 vote as Jonathan A. Harper.

sub_unit.note: John A. Harper received 2 votes as Josiah Harper and 1 vote as John Harper.

sub_unit.note: Samuel Dinsmore received 10 votes as Silas Dinsmore.

sub_unit.name: Stewartstown
sub_unit.note: Daniel Blaisdell received 1 vote as David Blasdel.

sub_unit.note: Josiah Bartlett received 2 votes as Joseph Bartlett.
